Happy Hanukkah to my Jewish friends. The historical miracle that the Holiday implicitly celebrates is the capacity to sustain intimate relations with another without totally ceding your own sense of self, the ability to love without permanently merging, to be enchanted by the

exquisite beauty of another without losing sight of your own charms. This relational art is ritualized on Hanukkah by the lighting of separate wicks or candles that build daily toward a unison of illumination. Isn’t that wonderful? Appreciating your own qualities while also
acknowledging someone else’s gifts. A template for Twitter? @jimcramer @tomkeene @lisaabramowicz1 @ferrotv @bloomberg @cnbcfastmoney @riskreversal @SaraEisen @ScottWapnerCNBC @carlquintanilla
